TITLE: Using Callback Functions with Term Class Map in Timber
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use a callback function with timber/term/classmap for conditional class selection. It selects between Genre and ComedyGenre classes based on the term ID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/timber/timber/blob/2.x/docs/v2/guides/class-maps.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use ComedyGenre;
use Genre;

add_filter('timber/term/classmap', function ($classmap) {
    $custom_classmap = [
        'genre' => function (\WP_Term $term) {
            if ($term->term_id === 2) {
                return ComedyGenre::class;
            }

            return Genre::class;
        },
    ];

    return array_merge($classmap, $custom_classmap);
});
```

